
# Commit messages should be readable by human and machine. To
# accomplish this goal all commit messages should follow v1.0.0 of the
# conventional commits specification.
#
# 50-character subject line.
# <type>[optional scope]: <description>
#
# 72-character wrapped longer optional body and optional footer.
# [optional body]
#
# [optional footer(s)]
#
# References:
# - https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/
#
# The body should answer:
#
# * Why was this change necessary?
# * How does it address the problem?
# * Are there any side effects?
#
# Use the footer when necessary per the spec.
#
# Additional references:
# - http://chris.beams.io/posts/git-commit/
